File: Increased shark sighting is common during this time of year with seals and fish close to shore. JOHANNESBURG - The National Sea Rescue Institute is appealing to surfers to be cautious along the Southern and Eastern Cape coastlines. A large number of shark sightings and some encounters have been reported over the past few weeks along the Plettenberg Bay coastline. READ: Shark bodies discovered on Strandfontein beach On Tuesday a Drone captured footage of a shark close to surfers. Increased shark sighting are common during this time of year with seals and fish close to shore.